    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-05-10T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-05-10T18:00:00-05:00" n="661"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d661">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 654.119/218</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SPA1"
                        type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stovall</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-05-10T19:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 10, 1918, 7 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1888. For <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_DEL1">Dresel</persName> [from
                    War Trade Board]:</p>
                <p>No. 18. Legation’s 3244, May 5, 11 a.m. [<hi rend="italic">3224, May 2, 3
                        p.m.</hi>], your 21.<note n="1" xml:id="d661fn1">Not printed.</note> Lumber
                    agreement and your signature thereto is approved. We will take under
                    consideration three suggestions recited.</p>
                <p>We have had surplus pork products during past two months, which surplus has now
                    disappeared. The Food Administration may therefore not be able to permit the
                    purchase of the total quantity of fats licensed. On account of great demand for
                    steel and other products, you should particularly advise us of any Swiss
                    applications for articles from United States which are for Allied purposes in
                    Switzerland. What are proposed limitation of imports of American, Egyptian, and
                    Indian cotton and what are limitations of exports under the new agreement?</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
